1
00:00:00,280 --> 00:00:01,420
Chapter 3.

2
00:00:01,420 --> 00:00:03,760
Blackjack Varn's Trick.

3
00:00:04,880 --> 00:00:06,800
Dust did not have time for a proper

4
00:00:06,800 --> 00:00:09,140
plan, so she settled for the kind that

5
00:00:09,140 --> 00:00:12,960
involved speed, rooftops, and a high chance of

6
00:00:12,960 --> 00:00:14,100
regretting things later.

7
00:00:14,100 --> 00:00:16,980
She rode Bishop straight through town.

8
00:00:17,740 --> 00:00:19,500
At the dry goods store, she stood in

9
00:00:19,500 --> 00:00:21,100
the stirrups and caught the edge of an

10
00:00:21,100 --> 00:00:21,600
awning.

11
00:00:22,120 --> 00:00:24,340
At the tailors, she climbed from awning to

12
00:00:24,340 --> 00:00:24,740
balcony.

13
00:00:24,740 --> 00:00:27,520
From the balcony, she hauled herself onto the

14
00:00:27,520 --> 00:00:29,180
roof of the boarding house.

15
00:00:29,180 --> 00:00:32,680
Someone below shouted, Marshall, that seems unsafe.

16
00:00:33,560 --> 00:00:36,680
Then don't copy me, she shouted back.

17
00:00:36,680 --> 00:00:39,420
Wind struck her as she reached the highest

18
00:00:39,420 --> 00:00:40,700
roof on Main Street.

19
00:00:41,260 --> 00:00:44,720
Up there, the floating stagecoach looked even stranger.

20
00:00:44,720 --> 00:00:47,240
The body was built like a rich man's

21
00:00:46,800 --> 00:00:50,140
travel coach, but brass pipes ran along its

22
00:00:50,140 --> 00:00:51,140
sides.

23
00:00:51,140 --> 00:00:53,240
Iron tanks clung to the rear axle.

24
00:00:53,240 --> 00:00:56,660
At the roofline, folded veins snapped in the

25
00:00:56,660 --> 00:00:58,460
wind like metal feathers.

26
00:00:58,460 --> 00:01:01,020
Smoke hissed from a crooked stack near the

27
00:01:01,020 --> 00:01:02,020
driver's box.

28
00:01:02,020 --> 00:01:03,980
It was not elegant.

29
00:01:03,980 --> 00:01:07,760
It was an airborne argument with common sense.

30
00:01:08,420 --> 00:01:10,360
The three fools on the saloon roof had

31
00:01:10,360 --> 00:01:12,900
finally managed to snag one rope around the

32
00:01:12,900 --> 00:01:13,640
back wheel.

33
00:01:13,940 --> 00:01:15,600
They cheered too early.

34
00:01:15,600 --> 00:01:18,580
The wheel spun, wrapped the rope, and yanked

35
00:01:18,580 --> 00:01:20,440
them belly first across the shingles in a

36
00:01:20,440 --> 00:01:21,900
single howling line.

37
00:01:21,900 --> 00:01:25,840
Dust stepped onto the saloon sign, balanced once,

38
00:01:25,840 --> 00:01:27,160
and judged the distance.

39
00:01:27,160 --> 00:01:30,480
This is going to be annoying, she told

40
00:01:30,480 --> 00:01:31,440
the sky.

41
00:01:31,440 --> 00:01:33,820
Then she jumped.

42
00:01:33,820 --> 00:01:36,980
For one terrible heartbeat, there was nothing under

43
00:01:36,980 --> 00:01:37,680
her boots.

44
00:01:37,680 --> 00:01:40,060
Then she hit the coach roof hard enough

45
00:01:40,060 --> 00:01:41,140
to bite her tongue.

46
00:01:41,760 --> 00:01:43,860
She slid halfway to the edge, grabbed a

47
00:01:43,860 --> 00:01:46,040
brass whale, and hauled herself flat while the

48
00:01:46,040 --> 00:01:47,960
coach rocked wildly.

49
00:01:47,960 --> 00:01:49,580
All right, she muttered.

50
00:01:49,580 --> 00:01:50,620
I'm here.

51
00:01:50,620 --> 00:01:51,900
Everybody can stop being dramatic.

52
00:01:53,180 --> 00:01:55,140
A hatch in the roof banged open below

53
00:01:55,140 --> 00:01:55,620
her.

54
00:01:55,900 --> 00:01:56,960
Steam belched upward.

55
00:01:57,880 --> 00:02:00,180
Dust dropped through into the coach.

56
00:02:00,740 --> 00:02:02,940
The inside looked like a gambling hall and

57
00:02:02,940 --> 00:02:04,880
a machine shop had gotten into a fistfight.

58
00:02:05,760 --> 00:02:07,540
Velvet seats were torn out to make room

59
00:02:07,540 --> 00:02:10,980
for gears, levers, gauges, and two large copper

60
00:02:10,980 --> 00:02:13,380
boilers that rattled with dangerous enthusiasm.

61
00:02:14,540 --> 00:02:16,700
Silver sacks were piled nearly to the ceiling.

62
00:02:17,820 --> 00:02:19,960
At the front, one man rustled to controls.

63
00:02:21,100 --> 00:02:23,640
Black Jack Varn wore black gloves, a black

64
00:02:23,640 --> 00:02:25,980
vest, and a grin so sharp it seemed

65
00:02:25,980 --> 00:02:27,160
like part of the weaponry.

66
00:02:27,680 --> 00:02:30,220
His hair was slicked back, his mustache curved

67
00:02:30,220 --> 00:02:32,620
like quotation marks around a joke nobody trusted.

68
00:02:33,680 --> 00:02:35,580
On his shoulder sat a green parrot with

69
00:02:35,580 --> 00:02:36,720
a missing tail feather.

70
00:02:37,480 --> 00:02:39,120
The parrot took one look at Dust and

71
00:02:39,120 --> 00:02:40,120
screamed, Law!

72
00:02:41,380 --> 00:02:43,640
Afternoon, Varn, Dust said.

73
00:02:44,120 --> 00:02:45,860
Black Jack Varn did not turn around right

74
00:02:45,860 --> 00:02:46,040
away.

75
00:02:46,560 --> 00:02:48,240
He only yanked a lever, cursed at a

76
00:02:48,240 --> 00:02:51,280
gauge, and said, Marshal Calloway, I ought to

77
00:02:51,280 --> 00:02:52,180
be insulted.

78
00:02:52,300 --> 00:02:54,480
You boarded my invention without buying a ticket.

79
00:02:55,380 --> 00:02:56,980
You dropped half your ticket money on the

80
00:02:56,980 --> 00:02:57,500
town.

81
00:02:58,220 --> 00:03:00,800
Now he looked over, his grin wild.

82
00:03:01,540 --> 00:03:03,360
Temporary complication.

83
00:03:04,240 --> 00:03:06,480
You call dynamite under the water tower temporary

84
00:03:06,480 --> 00:03:06,900
too?

85
00:03:07,860 --> 00:03:09,040
I call it insurance.

86
00:03:10,440 --> 00:03:12,240
Dust's hand drifted toward her revolver.

87
00:03:12,720 --> 00:03:14,100
Vor noticed and laughed.

88
00:03:14,780 --> 00:03:16,560
Go ahead and draw, he said.

89
00:03:17,140 --> 00:03:19,180
One stray shot and this one machine comes

90
00:03:19,180 --> 00:03:20,840
down in splinters and steam.

91
00:03:21,560 --> 00:03:22,360
Dust believed him.

92
00:03:23,320 --> 00:03:24,880
The coach bucked sideways.

93
00:03:25,200 --> 00:03:26,680
One of the boilers whined like it had

94
00:03:26,680 --> 00:03:28,180
seen the future and disliked it.

95
00:03:29,000 --> 00:03:30,040
You built this?

96
00:03:30,040 --> 00:03:31,200
Dusk asked.

97
00:03:31,760 --> 00:03:32,500
Designed it.

98
00:03:32,500 --> 00:03:33,200
Built it.

99
00:03:33,200 --> 00:03:34,120
Improved it.

100
00:03:34,640 --> 00:03:36,580
The roads belong to sheriffs and toll men

101
00:03:36,580 --> 00:03:37,160
and weather.

102
00:03:37,560 --> 00:03:39,560
The sky belongs to the first fool bold

103
00:03:39,560 --> 00:03:40,360
enough to take it.

104
00:03:41,260 --> 00:03:42,600
The parrot bobbed its head.

105
00:03:42,980 --> 00:03:43,780
Bold fool!

106
00:03:43,780 --> 00:03:44,740
Bold fool!

107
00:03:45,640 --> 00:03:46,960
Vaughn flecked a switch.

108
00:03:47,280 --> 00:03:49,400
The folded beams outside snap and vibrate.

109
00:03:49,700 --> 00:03:51,260
The coat clanged another few feet.

110
00:03:52,040 --> 00:03:53,960
You're not clean, you're friend.

111
00:03:54,140 --> 00:03:55,140
You're circling!

112
00:03:55,880 --> 00:03:58,760
I touched him, going scattered at the beach.

113
00:03:58,280 --> 00:04:01,480
Crosswind caught a speed-rise over the middle of

114
00:04:01,480 --> 00:04:01,920
the gorge.

115
00:04:01,840 --> 00:04:03,100
Nothing I can't say.

116
00:04:04,000 --> 00:04:05,800
Coach looked tall enough to knock a foot

117
00:04:05,800 --> 00:04:07,220
back into the wall.

118
00:04:07,700 --> 00:04:09,000
What a smile about you.

119
00:04:09,800 --> 00:04:11,480
You're a star-doller.

120
00:04:12,020 --> 00:04:13,820
Don't reach for another moment.

121
00:04:13,560 --> 00:04:15,460
Don't reach for a star-study.

122
00:04:15,900 --> 00:04:17,700
Get kids with the receptors you can use.

123
00:04:17,280 --> 00:04:19,120
You're not a good kid.

124
00:04:19,340 --> 00:04:20,720
You're a good kid.

125
00:04:21,780 --> 00:04:30,660
Thank

126
00:04:30,620 --> 00:04:59,480
you.

127
00:05:28,860 --> 00:05:30,760
So, Fast and dirty.

128
00:05:30,880 --> 00:05:32,840
Dust blocked one swing, took another to the

129
00:05:32,840 --> 00:05:34,700
ribs, and answered with a hard right that

130
00:05:34,700 --> 00:05:35,660
snapped his head sideways.

131
00:05:36,680 --> 00:05:38,260
He staggered into a wheel mounted on the

132
00:05:38,260 --> 00:05:38,780
front column.

133
00:05:39,700 --> 00:05:41,020
The parrot landed on top of it and

134
00:05:41,020 --> 00:05:42,280
shrieked, We're doomed!

135
00:05:43,680 --> 00:05:45,320
Outside, the green clouds thickened.

136
00:05:45,980 --> 00:05:47,700
Dust didn't notice them before from the street,

137
00:05:47,800 --> 00:05:49,140
but up here they looked worse.

138
00:05:49,540 --> 00:05:52,040
A spinning storm wall, green as bottle glass,

139
00:05:52,180 --> 00:05:54,020
rolling in low over the plains.

140
00:05:54,580 --> 00:05:56,060
Vaughn wiped blood from the corner of his

141
00:05:56,060 --> 00:05:56,780
mouth.

142
00:05:57,140 --> 00:05:59,480
He'll paint a bad time to interfere, Marshall.

143
00:06:00,360 --> 00:06:01,980
Dust glanced through the front glass.

144
00:06:02,480 --> 00:06:03,440
No, she said.

145
00:06:03,880 --> 00:06:05,660
You picked a bad day to fly.
